subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Orange submarginal band of wings upperside strongly reduced in both sexes, only 2–3 spots developed near tornal lobe (band usually well developed in 

A. phoenicura

); thin silvery line extends from tornus midway along to outer margin (line poorly developed near tornal lobe in 

A. phoenicura

); inner black strokes of submarginal orange band of wings underside reduced on both wings (well developed in 

A. phoenicura

); valva widened, with rounded apex and developed inner fold (valva narrowed with indented apex and smaller inner fold in 

A. phoenicura

); aedeagus strongly curved, crescent (aedeagus slightly curved in 

A. phoenicura

).
